'''''Nu da şpagă''''' ("Don't Bribe" in [[Romanian language|Romanian]]) is a national anti-[[political corruption|corruption]] campaign launched in [[Romania]] in 2004 to deal with the problem of corruption in that country. The campaign is co-ordinated by [[Transparency International]] with the support of the [[European Union]], which Romania joined in 2007. Corruption has been a problem in Romania since [[Communist Romania|Communist times]], but the situation has recently improved.{{citation needed|date=October 2012}}

