The '''Rhoda and Bernard Sarnat International Prize in Mental Health''' was established in 1992 and is awarded annually by the [[National Academy of Medicine]] in the United States to recognize individuals, groups, or organizations for outstanding achievement in improving mental health. It is accompanied by a medal and $20,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nam.edu/about-the-nam/the-rhoda-and-bernard-sarnat-international-prize-in-mental-health/|title=The Rhoda and Bernard Sarnat International Prize in Mental Health|publisher=National Academy of Sciences|accessdate= 7 November 2016}}</ref>
